page.title: 01HIGH WYCOMBE
page.content: {High Wycombe}has developed alongside the{River Wye}at a gap in the{Chiltern {Hills,}29 miles from London and 26 miles from Oxford.In the twelfth centuary it was a{market town.}Later it was successively known for wool, lace and the{furniture industry. Today it is a centre for electronics and light engineering.It is a commuter town,the train journey to London taking 45 minutes.The{older {residential areas}around the town centre were mainly occupied by people whose families have lived there for many generations although many of these houses are now occupied by Asians and West Indians who,since 1965, have grown into a substantial community.Old factories and smaller industrial units co-exist in this area.
